title: Tampa Bay Benthic Index
text: Tampa Bay Benthic Index (TBBI) [1,2]) assessment method quantifies ecological health benthic community Tampa Bay. index provides complementary approach evaluating environmental condition supported assessment methods currently available region (e.g., water quality report card, nekton index, etc.). tbeptools package includes several functions described import data required index plot results view trends time. functions described detail . TBBI uses data Tampa Bay Benthic Monitoring Program part Environmental Protection Commission (EPC) Hillsborough Country. data updated annually public site maintained EPC, typically December Summer/Fall sampling. website hosts water quality data used water quality report card. required data TBBI extensive water quality report card data made available zipped folder csv files, available . process downloading working data similar functions tbeptools.

text: Metrics scores Tampa Bay Nekton Index can calculated using two functions. anlz_tbnimet() function calculates raw metrics anlz_tbniscr() function calculates scored metrics final TBNI score. functions use imported formatted FIM data input. text: Functions tbeptools three categories based mode use. function named using prefix mode use, followed function . prefixes : read: Import current data main site. anlz: Analyze summarize imported data. show: Create plot analyzed data. functions can easily found RStudio loading package typing prefix command line. autofill dialog box pop showing functions apply prefix. eliminates need searching individual functions know category function need (e.g., read, anlz, show). function also includes semi-descriptive suffix generally describes category applies (e.g, water quality, seagrass) (e.g., imports, formats). follow loose convention attempts strike balance description brevity. optimal balance often hard achieve. aid understanding, provide brief description suffixes used . Suffix descriptions: attain: Analyze functions summarize data relative attainment categories specific bay segments ave, med: Analyze functions summarize data averages medians benthic: Applies benthic monitoring data used Tampa Bay Benthic Index fim: Applies data Fisheries Independent Monitoring program used Tampa Bay Nekton Index form: intermediate function formatting imported data downstream analysis hmp: Functions work Habitat Master Plan data import: function used import data source external package indic: function analyzes plots individual tidal creek indicator values, opposed integrated creek scores iwr: Functions data apply Impaired Waters Rule (IWR) data maintained Florida Department Environmental Protection used source data tidal creek functions matrix: plotting function creates report card style matrix met: function analyses plots individual metrics integrated indices, e.g., TBBI, TBNI phyto: Applies phytoplankton data Hillsborough County Environmental Protection Commission plotly: plotting function returns interactive plotly object scr: function analyses plots summary scores integrated indices, e.g., TBBI, TBNI seg, site: Functions analyze plot results relative bay segments individual monitoring sites tbbi: Applies Tampa Bay Benthic Index (TBBI) tbni: Applies Tampa Bay Nekton Index (TBNI) tdlcrk: Applies tidal creeks transect: Applies seagrass transect data wq: Applies water quality function reference page can also viewed complete list functions organized category, description , links help files. following example demonstrates use subset functions water quality data read file Hillsborough County Environmental Protection Commission long-term monitoring dataset (available https://www.tampabay.wateratlas.usf.edu/), analyze monthly annual averages major bay segments Tampa Bay, plot annual time series one bay segments.  Functions tbeptools also support creation content interactive, online dashboards can facilitate informed decisions without requiring intimate understanding R programming language methods analysis. dashboards include assessments water quality, seagrasses, nekton communities, tidal creeks.

Nitrogen ratios given year reflect ratio median nitrogen concentrations measured source tidal segment day.  Note ratio one can obtained source tidal segments minimum detection. Indicators years 10% observations exceed saturation criteria also estimated.  do_bnml do_prop columns show 1 0 given year indicate ten percent observations percent saturation 42.  first column based binomial probability exceedance takes account number observations year second column based simple proportional estimate raw data. radar = TRUE, output returned format use show_tdlcrkradar  Specifically, results calculated percentage years indicator exceeds relevant threshold.  applies marine WBIDs tidal creeks (Florida DEP class 2, 3M).  Six indicators returned percentage exceedances based total nitrogen (tn_ind) greater 1.1 mg/L, chlorophyll (chla_ind) greater 11 ug/L, trophic state index (tsi_ind) greater 55 (100), nitrate/nitrite ratio marine upstream segments (nox_ind) greater one, chlorophyll total nitrogen ratios > 15, percentage years ten percent observations percent saturation 42.

title: Format water quality and station metadata from the Water Quality Portal — read_formwqp
code: if (FALSE) { url <- list(   Result = "https://www.waterqualitydata.us/data/Result/search?mimeType=csv&zip=no",   Station = "https://www.waterqualitydata.us/data/Station/search?mimeType=csv&zip=no" )  headers <- c(   "Content-Type" = "application/json",   "Accept" = "application/zip" )  body <- list(   organization = c("21FLMANA_WQX"),   sampleMedia = c("Water"),   characteristicType = c("Information", "Nutrient", "Biological, Algae, Phytoplankton,     Photosynthetic Pigments"),   providers = c("STORET"),   siteType = c("Estuary") )  res <- url[['Result']] %>%   httr::POST(httr::add_headers(headers), body = jsonlite::toJSON(body)) %>%   httr::content('text') %>%   read.csv(text = .)  sta <- url[['Station']] %>%   httr::POST(httr::add_headers(headers), body = jsonlite::toJSON(body)) %>%   httr::content('text') %>%   read.csv(text = .)  # combine and format read_formwqp(res, sta, 'Manatee', '21FLMANA_WQX') }
